#week-title("Four", "Cohobating over Mineral Salt with Vegetable Sulphur as Medium")

=== Core Teaching

This week the student combines the Month 7 border cohobation work with the
Month 10 Sulphur work: a rectified vegetable Sulphur fraction (or concentrated
wine vinegar) is used as the medium for a cohobation over a mineral salt
substrate.

This is the most advanced preparation in Year Two and the most direct
anticipation of Year Three's mineral work. The sequence:

1. Mineral salt (salt of tartar or prepared sea salt) as the fixed base
2. Rectified vegetable Sulphur (or strong wine vinegar) as the active medium
3. Gentle digestion in a sealed vessel over two to three weeks

The Sulphur fraction, carrying the characterising virtue of its source plant,
now acts upon the mineral salt in a different manner than the plain Mercury
fraction or hydrosol would. The corrosive sharpness of the Sulphur (especially
in the vinegar form) partially opens the mineral salt — begins to dissolve and
unlock its structure — allowing the vegetable virtue to penetrate more deeply
than would otherwise be possible.

*The Anima Mundi connection.* Thomas Vaughan teaches that the Anima Mundi —
the World Soul — is the animating spirit within the Spiritus Mundi. When the
three principles of a substance are genuinely cohobated at a higher level,
what is produced is a localised intensification of the World Soul within
the prepared body. The vegetable Sulphur working upon the mineral Salt is,
in this understanding, the World Soul's vegetable expression penetrating the
mineral kingdom's crystallised structure — planting the living principle
within the fixed.

This is philosophically the same act as the Plant Stone's formation, but
crossing kingdoms: not vegetable upon vegetable (Year One) but vegetable upon
mineral (Year Two border work). Year Three will reverse this: mineral upon
mineral, in its own proper terms.

*Record keeping is essential.* Document the preparation fully: source of the
mineral salt, source and degree of rectification of the Sulphur, date of
sealing, initial observations, and a note of the philosophical intention behind
the work.

=== Topics This Week

- The vegetable-Sulphur-upon-mineral-salt cohobation: a full border preparation
- Vaughan's Anima Mundi: the vegetable principle animating the mineral structure
- Completing the Year Two progression: vegetable → water → vegetable-mineral border
- Documentation and Materia Medica update for all Month 10 work

#inner-work[
  *The World Soul as Practitioner*

  Vaughan's teaching places the practitioner in a specific position: they are
  the hands through which the Anima Mundi works upon matter. The preparation is
  not something the practitioner does to a substance — it is something the World
  Soul does through the practitioner upon the substance.

  Sit with this contemplation for twenty minutes before the final sealing of
  this month's preparation. Does it change the quality of your attention to
  approach the work as a participant in the World Soul's own process, rather
  than as an operator performing a technique? Record what arises.
]

